1
00:00:07,654 --> 00:00:10,657
[car engine revving]

2
00:00:11,325 --> 00:00:14,328
[dog barking]

3
00:00:18,707 --> 00:00:20,917
[slurping]

4
00:00:21,835 --> 00:00:22,836
[car engine shuts off]

5
00:00:25,672 --> 00:00:26,882
[car door opens]

6
00:00:26,965 --> 00:00:28,925
Hey, come here.
Help me take care of this.

7
00:00:38,935 --> 00:00:40,187
[Farmer exhales]

8
00:00:40,270 --> 00:00:42,689
[Farmer] What is this?
You didn't chop it up?

9
00:00:43,732 --> 00:00:45,275
What am I supposed to do with it?

10
00:00:45,359 --> 00:00:48,403
Well, I got into some shit.
Help a brother out.

11
00:00:48,487 --> 00:00:50,322
Nobody told me.

12
00:00:51,782 --> 00:00:52,908
You're from Yes Money?

13
00:00:52,991 --> 00:00:55,035
Course I am.
We've met a few times already.

14
00:00:55,118 --> 00:00:57,079
Moonsu and the other guys aren't with you?

15
00:00:57,162 --> 00:00:58,955
Moonsu?

16
00:00:59,373 --> 00:01:02,417
Moonsu's probably at work right now.
Duh.

17
00:01:05,337 --> 00:01:06,421
[exhales sharply]

18
00:01:06,838 --> 00:01:08,507
[Woogy] Just do me this favor.

19
00:01:15,555 --> 00:01:16,807
[exhales]

20
00:01:16,890 --> 00:01:18,475
[Farmer grunts]

21
00:01:19,226 --> 00:01:21,561
[Farmer] Who the fuck brings uncut meat?

22
00:01:23,146 --> 00:01:26,149
[bag scraping]

23
00:01:28,944 --> 00:01:30,362
I appreciate this!

24
00:01:31,279 --> 00:01:34,866
[machine buzzing and clanging]

25
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:37,577
[bones crunching]

26
00:01:39,121 --> 00:01:41,081
[pigs snorting]

27
00:01:48,755 --> 00:01:50,966
[slop squelching]

28
00:01:51,049 --> 00:01:54,052
[crows cawing]

29
00:02:02,811 --> 00:02:04,855
[Heeju breathing heavily]

30
00:02:06,565 --> 00:02:07,566
[knock at door]

31
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:08,650
[gasps]

32
00:02:09,609 --> 00:02:12,612
[knocking continues]

33
00:02:20,746 --> 00:02:23,540
[door creaks]

34
00:02:23,623 --> 00:02:26,376
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

35
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:27,461
Heeju.

36
00:02:29,838 --> 00:02:30,839
I'm hungry.

37
00:02:31,631 --> 00:02:32,716
[chuckles]

38
00:02:33,675 --> 00:02:35,761
[Woogy] Oh, I'm so fucking starving
right now!

39
00:02:36,261 --> 00:02:37,304
[Woogy groans]

40
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:39,681
[door locks]

41
00:02:41,099 --> 00:02:43,018
[broth splashing]

42
00:02:43,101 --> 00:02:46,104
[exhales heavily]

43
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:48,774
[slurping]

44
00:02:48,857 --> 00:02:52,569
[slurping continues]

45
00:02:53,695 --> 00:02:54,696
[huffing]

46
00:02:59,409 --> 00:03:02,412
[Woogy slurping]

47
00:03:02,788 --> 00:03:03,955
[Woogy exhales]

48
00:03:07,417 --> 00:03:09,377
Ah.

49
00:03:12,172 --> 00:03:13,173
[exhales]

50
00:03:14,966 --> 00:03:15,967
Heeju.

51
00:03:17,844 --> 00:03:19,387
You know, my dad...

52
00:03:21,264 --> 00:03:22,849
...he was the same kind
of asshole as your uncle.

53
00:03:24,392 --> 00:03:26,269
He brought our whole family down
with his gambling addiction.

54
00:03:27,437 --> 00:03:29,231
That piece of shit should
have just died alone.

55
00:03:29,856 --> 00:03:31,525
He even tried to kill my mom and I.

56
00:03:33,568 --> 00:03:34,569
Anyway...

57
00:03:40,116 --> 00:03:41,326
[Woogy] Don't give it another though.

58
00:03:42,285 --> 00:03:43,537
[Woogy] I took care of the body.

59
00:03:44,788 --> 00:03:46,748
[Woogy] There's not a single shred
of flesh left.

60
00:03:46,831 --> 00:03:48,083
Don't worry about it.

61
00:03:49,626 --> 00:03:50,794
[grunts]

62
00:03:54,256 --> 00:03:56,508
This one?
This one's mine?

63
00:04:03,723 --> 00:04:05,350
I said don't worry!

64
00:04:08,144 --> 00:04:09,145
Just let it go.

65
00:04:09,229 --> 00:04:10,230
[smacks lips]

66
00:04:12,691 --> 00:04:15,527
[Woogy] I mean, that was a man
who deserved to die.

67
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,240
[Heeju] A man who deserved to die?

68
00:04:21,032 --> 00:04:22,033
[Woogy] Mm-hmm.

69
00:04:23,326 --> 00:04:24,619
[exhales]

70
00:04:25,579 --> 00:04:26,580
Hey.

71
00:04:28,248 --> 00:04:30,125
You see how important money is now?
STYLE
::cue()

72
00:04:32,294 --> 00:04:33,837
It makes the world go 'round.

73
00:04:35,589 --> 00:04:38,842
Like, having money lets you do
anything you could ever want.

74
00:04:38,925 --> 00:04:41,845
[Woogy] And it also lets you
not do things you don't want.

75
00:04:43,722 --> 00:04:44,806
[Woogy] Oh, yeah.

76
00:04:45,807 --> 00:04:48,476
[Woogy] Here you go.
As promised.

77
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,561
[Woogy] Your new ID card.

78
00:04:49,644 --> 00:04:51,396
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
JU HARAN

79
00:04:51,479 --> 00:04:52,480
I just went through all our debtors,

80
00:04:52,564 --> 00:04:54,316
and then I picked out who looked
like you the most.

81
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:57,068
[Woogy] We can take care of the passport
and fingerprints and all that later.

82
00:04:57,152 --> 00:05:00,780
[Woogy] But for starters,
open a bank account under her name.

83
00:05:02,032 --> 00:05:05,160
Well, obviously we're about
to have piles of cash rollin' in.

84
00:05:05,452 --> 00:05:08,079
So, can't exactly keep
it all piled up in here.

85
00:05:08,371 --> 00:05:09,372
Hmm?

86
00:05:09,456 --> 00:05:11,166
Who is this lady?

87
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,918
[Woogy] Ah, this lady...

88
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,921
...she's dead.

89
00:05:17,422 --> 00:05:18,506
It was suicide.

90
00:05:19,174 --> 00:05:20,175
A year ago.

91
00:05:21,968 --> 00:05:23,094
So they say.

92
00:05:25,513 --> 00:05:27,724
[Woogy] She doesn't exist in
the world anymore.

93
00:05:27,807 --> 00:05:30,560
No one is looking for her,
and there's no way to find her.

94
00:05:30,644 --> 00:05:32,395
[Woogy] And someone that young...

95
00:05:33,355 --> 00:05:36,524
...you really think she had any money?
They took her organs.

96
00:05:36,608 --> 00:05:39,402
[Woogy] She just doesn't exist.
She's gone.

97
00:05:42,405 --> 00:05:46,242
I'll also turn out like that,
if I get caught by your company people.

98
00:05:48,745 --> 00:05:49,955
So be good.

99
00:05:51,665 --> 00:05:52,666
Or else.

100
00:05:55,669 --> 00:05:57,379
[chuckles]

101
00:05:57,462 --> 00:05:59,965
Anyway, we need to wrap
this whole thing up quickly.

102
00:06:00,048 --> 00:06:03,343
[Woogy] Since Detective Kim
is even involved now,

103
00:06:03,426 --> 00:06:04,469
it's a huge deal.

104
00:06:04,552 --> 00:06:07,097
I bet the guys at Yes Money
are desperate to find you.

105
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:08,181
What do we do?

106
00:06:08,974 --> 00:06:11,017
[Woogy] We got eight potatoes left, right?

107
00:06:11,101 --> 00:06:13,228
Let's craft and sell two
at a time now.

108
00:06:14,104 --> 00:06:17,857
After selling so many one-kilo bars,
I realized how fucking easy it is.

109
00:06:17,941 --> 00:06:19,275
If I just run my ass off,

110
00:06:19,359 --> 00:06:20,902
hitting all the jewelry shops,

111
00:06:20,986 --> 00:06:22,362
I can sell 20 in three days.

112
00:06:22,696 --> 00:06:23,947
[Woogy] It could be done in two weeks.

113
00:06:24,531 --> 00:06:25,532
[Woogy] In the meantime,

114
00:06:25,615 --> 00:06:27,409
you should get your passport ready to go.

115
00:06:27,492 --> 00:06:29,703
Then we'll go overseas.
Simple.

116
00:06:33,164 --> 00:06:34,165
What is it?

117
00:06:36,543 --> 00:06:38,670
You still don't trust me after all this?

118
00:06:39,629 --> 00:06:40,630
[Woogy] Heeju.

119
00:06:41,214 --> 00:06:43,591
[Woogy] We're way past being
just business partners now.

120
00:06:44,968 --> 00:06:47,053
I even killed a man because of you.

121
00:06:48,763 --> 00:06:50,682
We're like bound by fate now.

122
00:06:50,765 --> 00:06:51,891
[chuckles]

123
00:06:51,975 --> 00:06:53,393
Bound by fate.

124
00:06:53,476 --> 00:06:54,769
[Woogy chuckles]

125
00:06:54,853 --> 00:06:56,312
[Woogy] I better get going.

126
00:06:58,064 --> 00:06:59,858
How many potatoes
are you bringing next round?

127
00:06:59,941 --> 00:07:01,151
Two.

128
00:07:01,234 --> 00:07:03,319
Correct.
Where do they need to go?

129
00:07:03,403 --> 00:07:05,071
To the shop.

130
00:07:05,155 --> 00:07:06,865
Correct.
Where do you get those?

131
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,118
I guess not. Okay.

132
00:07:10,201 --> 00:07:11,619
You're too smart!

133
00:07:11,703 --> 00:07:13,121
I'm out.

134
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,249
Ah, fuck, I'm so tired.

135
00:07:16,332 --> 00:07:18,501
[Woogy chuckles]

136
00:07:18,585 --> 00:07:20,587
[door creaks closed]

137
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:23,673
[distant car engine rumbling]

138
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:28,553
[clock ticking echoing]

139
00:07:33,975 --> 00:07:36,978
[♪ sad piano music]

140
00:08:01,127 --> 00:08:04,130
[♪ music continues]

141
00:08:16,184 --> 00:08:19,771
EPISODE 5
SECRET

142
00:08:19,854 --> 00:08:21,648
JANGGAK TRADE INC.

143
00:08:21,731 --> 00:08:23,525
[Donggu] Can I help you?

144
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:26,820
Uh, hi.
I want to buy a car today.

145
00:08:26,903 --> 00:08:27,904
You're here to get a car?

146
00:08:27,987 --> 00:08:29,489
-[Heeju] Yes.
-Ah.

147
00:08:29,572 --> 00:08:31,241
How did you hear about us?

148
00:08:31,324 --> 00:08:33,201
I run a pawnshop.

149
00:08:33,868 --> 00:08:34,911
You run a pawnshop?

150
00:08:34,994 --> 00:08:37,205
-[grunts]
-[Donggu] All right.

151
00:08:38,289 --> 00:08:40,250
Let me show you our cars.

152
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:42,877
-Okay.
-Any particular type car you had in mind?

153
00:08:42,961 --> 00:08:44,379
Uh, no, not really.

154
00:08:44,462 --> 00:08:46,047
No, okay then.

155
00:08:46,131 --> 00:08:47,132
Well, if that's the case,

156
00:08:47,215 --> 00:08:49,926
then this one here
is probably what you're looking for.

157
00:08:50,009 --> 00:08:51,803
[Donggu] It has good mileage,
plus it's practically brand new.

158
00:08:51,886 --> 00:08:53,096
Huh.

159
00:08:53,179 --> 00:08:55,306
[machine rattling]

160
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:59,310
[Donggu] Now all you gotta do is take this
to the district office

161
00:08:59,394 --> 00:09:00,812
and transfer the title.

162
00:09:00,895 --> 00:09:02,188
-Okay.
-Here.
STYLE
::cue()

163
00:09:03,106 --> 00:09:05,775
-You can take the car today.
-Thanks.

164
00:09:05,859 --> 00:09:09,779
Actually, I was curious
about your pawnshop.

165
00:09:09,863 --> 00:09:11,072
[stammers]

166
00:09:11,156 --> 00:09:14,117
Is it here around the Jeongsan area?

167
00:09:14,951 --> 00:09:15,952
[exhales]

168
00:09:16,035 --> 00:09:17,412
Why do you ask?

169
00:09:17,495 --> 00:09:20,498
It's just that there's not
a pawnshop I don't know around here.

170
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,836
It was originally run by a relative,
and something came up,

171
00:09:24,919 --> 00:09:26,629
so I ended up taking it over.

172
00:09:26,713 --> 00:09:27,964
Ah.

173
00:09:28,047 --> 00:09:31,176
I was wondering,
where do all the cars end up going?

174
00:09:31,259 --> 00:09:33,553
Most of 'em?
Eh...

175
00:09:34,971 --> 00:09:36,347
[Donggu] Most of 'em end up overseas.

176
00:09:36,431 --> 00:09:38,850
What about the other collateral,
besides the cars?

177
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:42,061
Those other items normally end up
overseas, too.

178
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,521
More or less.

179
00:09:43,605 --> 00:09:47,233
[Heeju] You only ship items overseas
and don't ship anything back in?

180
00:09:50,236 --> 00:09:52,906
For a young lady,
you sure are curious about all this.

181
00:09:53,615 --> 00:09:54,616
-Uh...
-[Donggu] I mean,

182
00:09:54,699 --> 00:09:56,075
you're askin' a lot of questions.

183
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:58,578
Are you a cop
or someone from customs?

184
00:09:58,661 --> 00:10:01,080
No, it's nothing like that.
I'm just really curious.

185
00:10:01,164 --> 00:10:02,165
Actually, up until recently,

186
00:10:02,248 --> 00:10:05,126
I used to be in a similar line
of work as you.

187
00:10:05,210 --> 00:10:07,545
Checking imported goods,
clearing them for entry.

188
00:10:10,298 --> 00:10:12,175
Oh, really?

189
00:10:12,258 --> 00:10:15,053
Uh, one more thing.

190
00:10:16,304 --> 00:10:19,140
We've had this for a while,
just hanging around the pawnshop.

191
00:10:20,725 --> 00:10:25,730
[Heeju] And I was wondering
if you had any bullets for it.

192
00:10:26,773 --> 00:10:30,401
It's just sometimes working late
nights alone can be kinda scary.

193
00:10:31,569 --> 00:10:32,612
[Heeju] Hopefully I never have to use it,

194
00:10:32,695 --> 00:10:35,865
but just having it would make
me feel so much safer.

195
00:10:36,783 --> 00:10:39,035
Yeah. Is that so?

196
00:10:39,577 --> 00:10:40,662
You're a surprising young lady.

197
00:10:41,704 --> 00:10:43,248
I can give you however much you want.

198
00:10:43,331 --> 00:10:45,083
[Donggu] It's not about the money.

199
00:10:45,166 --> 00:10:47,043
Smuggling is just not what I do.

200
00:10:48,878 --> 00:10:50,672
Is it that you can't,
or that you won't?

201
00:10:50,755 --> 00:10:51,756
[Donggu chuckles nervously]

202
00:10:51,839 --> 00:10:53,508
Listen, I'm guessing since
you're new in town,

203
00:10:53,591 --> 00:10:55,218
you haven't heard of me before.

204
00:10:55,301 --> 00:10:56,886
Do I look like someone who can't to you?

205
00:10:56,970 --> 00:10:58,429
Maybe I just don't wanna.

206
00:10:58,513 --> 00:11:01,349
I was thinking if you
could get this for me,

207
00:11:01,432 --> 00:11:03,643
then there could be other things
you could help me with.

208
00:11:03,726 --> 00:11:04,978
[inhales sharply]

209
00:11:05,061 --> 00:11:07,063
However, if it's something
that you don't do, then...

210
00:11:08,982 --> 00:11:11,859
What other sort of things
did you need help with?

211
00:11:11,943 --> 00:11:14,612
Well, I don't know.

212
00:11:14,696 --> 00:11:17,031
There's nothing that
a pawnshop doesn't have.

213
00:11:19,909 --> 00:11:20,910
Detonics.

214
00:11:22,745 --> 00:11:24,289
Wait here a second while
I go get them for you.

215
00:11:29,419 --> 00:11:30,586
[door opens and shuts]

216
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:32,672
[inhales and exhales sharply]

217
00:11:34,465 --> 00:11:35,967
[door opens and shuts]

218
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:38,177
[Donggu breathing heavily]

219
00:11:38,261 --> 00:11:39,262
[grunts]

220
00:11:40,179 --> 00:11:42,098
So, have you fired a gun?

221
00:11:42,181 --> 00:11:43,641
Uh, no.

222
00:11:44,642 --> 00:11:47,270
It's not like I'd actually have
a reason to use it.

223
00:11:47,353 --> 00:11:48,438
Uh-huh.

224
00:11:49,022 --> 00:11:50,982
First insert the magazine.

225
00:11:51,065 --> 00:11:52,233
[magazine clicks]

226
00:11:52,317 --> 00:11:54,277
[Donggu] Like that.
After that,

227
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,280
you grab this part and slide it back.

228
00:11:57,363 --> 00:11:58,823
[Donggu] When you do that,

229
00:11:58,906 --> 00:12:00,908
a bullet will be chambered here.

230
00:12:00,992 --> 00:12:02,535
And since it's very dangerous,

231
00:12:02,618 --> 00:12:04,871
you need to always keep the safety up,

232
00:12:04,954 --> 00:12:07,040
like so,
until you need to fire.

233
00:12:07,498 --> 00:12:08,916
It's the same with the trigger.

234
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,086
Until you're ready,
your finger stays back here.

235
00:12:13,004 --> 00:12:14,047
[Donggu] And when you shoot,

236
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:17,133
always hold it with both hands.

237
00:12:17,508 --> 00:12:18,634
Just like so.

238
00:12:18,718 --> 00:12:21,054
[Donggu] Most women find
the recoil pretty strong.

239
00:12:22,013 --> 00:12:24,223
You see this?
This waving?

240
00:12:24,974 --> 00:12:27,477
Any sort of movement affects
your accuracy.

241
00:12:28,561 --> 00:12:29,645
[Donggu] The head and heart.

242
00:12:29,729 --> 00:12:32,273
That's where you aim,
and if you don't hit them there,

243
00:12:32,357 --> 00:12:34,567
you keep shooting until they're dead.

244
00:12:34,650 --> 00:12:36,194
-Bang!
- [gasps]

245
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:38,154
[Donggu] Bang, bang.
Bang, bang.

246
00:12:38,946 --> 00:12:41,115
You want to kill,
you keep shooting.

247
00:12:42,158 --> 00:12:43,159
Here.

248
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,163
How much money do I owe you?

249
00:12:47,246 --> 00:12:48,456
Ah, no, no, no, no.

250
00:12:48,539 --> 00:12:50,708
I don't need money.
It's a gift from me to you.

251
00:12:52,085 --> 00:12:57,673
In return, how about from now on,
you only work with me?

252
00:13:10,728 --> 00:13:13,731
[car engine rumbling]

253
00:13:14,649 --> 00:13:15,733
[clicks tongue]

254
00:13:15,817 --> 00:13:17,026
[exhales]

255
00:13:21,906 --> 00:13:23,074
NAME JU HARAN
STYLE
::cue()

256
00:13:28,579 --> 00:13:31,582
[♪ dramatic piano music]

257
00:13:42,635 --> 00:13:44,470
[shovel digging]

258
00:13:44,554 --> 00:13:45,555
[grunts]

259
00:13:53,855 --> 00:13:55,231
[Heeju grunts]

260
00:14:08,077 --> 00:14:09,120
[gold bars clinking]

261
00:14:09,203 --> 00:14:10,913
[Heeju grunting]

262
00:14:12,623 --> 00:14:15,585
[Heeju] There's no one in this world
who deserves to die.

263
00:14:17,003 --> 00:14:18,754
I killed so I can live.

264
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,631
That's all it is.

265
00:14:20,715 --> 00:14:22,091
[groans]

266
00:14:22,175 --> 00:14:24,343
[Heeju] Because I can't be
the one to die.

267
00:14:32,226 --> 00:14:33,227
[blows hard]

268
00:14:35,938 --> 00:14:36,981
[exhales]

269
00:14:38,566 --> 00:14:39,609
[Heeju grunts]

270
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,281
[breathing heavily]

271
00:14:45,364 --> 00:14:48,367
[car engine rumbling]

272
00:14:49,535 --> 00:14:50,786
[grunts]

273
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:53,164
[breathing heavily]

274
00:15:00,046 --> 00:15:01,172
[brakes squeak]

275
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:08,471
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

276
00:15:20,483 --> 00:15:22,276
-[Sunok exhales]
-[Heeju] Auntie.

277
00:15:24,111 --> 00:15:25,238
[Heeju] How are you doing?

278
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,573
[Sunok grunts]

279
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:32,036
-[Sunok groans lightly]
-Yes?

280
00:15:32,119 --> 00:15:33,329
[Sunok exhales]

281
00:15:34,789 --> 00:15:36,249
[Sunok] Why are you still here?

282
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:38,167
You should lie down.

283
00:15:39,377 --> 00:15:40,503
The cash I gave you.

284
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:42,463
Did you return it?

285
00:15:44,215 --> 00:15:45,424
Is that...

286
00:15:45,508 --> 00:15:47,009
[Sunok] ...why he dropped the charges?

287
00:15:48,552 --> 00:15:49,679
Mm-hmm.

288
00:15:49,762 --> 00:15:50,846
[Sunok] You crazy bitch.

289
00:15:51,764 --> 00:15:53,474
Why didn't you run when I told you to?

290
00:15:53,557 --> 00:15:54,475
[shudders]

291
00:15:54,558 --> 00:15:55,977
You need to run away.

292
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,687
Go quickly,
before he comes back.

293
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:58,771
It's all right.

294
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,565
That man won't ever come back again.

295
00:16:02,149 --> 00:16:03,734
I'm telling you, he will!

296
00:16:04,944 --> 00:16:06,779
And then the both of us
will be trapped here.

297
00:16:07,822 --> 00:16:10,950
He's already bleeding me dry.
That's more than enough.

298
00:16:12,285 --> 00:16:13,369
You-you have to go now.

299
00:16:13,452 --> 00:16:14,912
I don't have to.

300
00:16:16,372 --> 00:16:19,000
It's not like I have much time left.
I don't need you. Just hurry up and go.

301
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:21,210
Aunty, that's why I'm not leaving you.

302
00:16:22,628 --> 00:16:25,631
What'll it take, then?
Should I hang myself?

303
00:16:25,715 --> 00:16:27,758
-[Sunok] Listen to me!
-No!

304
00:16:27,842 --> 00:16:30,219
[distant footsteps approaching]

305
00:16:32,221 --> 00:16:33,472
He has to be coming.

306
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:37,351
He's coming, I said!

307
00:16:38,019 --> 00:16:39,562
You-you need to hide somewhere.

308
00:16:39,645 --> 00:16:41,480
-Look at me. Stop.
-[Sunok] Quickly.

309
00:16:41,564 --> 00:16:44,442
-You have to hide-
-[Heeju] Auntie. Auntie. Auntie.

310
00:16:45,568 --> 00:16:49,113
That asshole is never coming back.

311
00:16:50,072 --> 00:16:51,907
He can't come back.

312
00:16:53,617 --> 00:16:54,660
[Heeju exhales deeply]

313
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:58,331
This time I made sure of that so now...

314
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,043
...everything's gonna be okay.

315
00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:11,093
From now on,
I'll stay by your side.

316
00:17:11,677 --> 00:17:14,680
[Sunok inhales and exhales deeply]
STYLE
::cue()

317
00:17:18,851 --> 00:17:21,854
[distant sirens wailing]

318
00:17:23,314 --> 00:17:25,232
[Thai Businessman] My chairman's
losing patience now.

319
00:17:25,316 --> 00:17:27,276
All these construction delays.

320
00:17:28,444 --> 00:17:30,363
[Woojin speaking Korean]

321
00:17:32,406 --> 00:17:38,412
[speaking Korean]

322
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:45,461
There are formal
legal protocols to follow.

323
00:17:45,544 --> 00:17:49,256
Once your chairman signs off,
we're ready to move immediately.

324
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:51,050
Well, for that to happen,

325
00:17:51,133 --> 00:17:53,052
we're going to need a solid guarantee
from you guys.

326
00:17:53,135 --> 00:17:55,930
[speaking Korean]

327
00:17:57,014 --> 00:18:01,769
[Thai Businessman] Let's just say
we'll need a reason to move.

328
00:18:01,852 --> 00:18:03,437
[speaking Korean]

329
00:18:13,739 --> 00:18:15,157
What did he just say?

330
00:18:15,241 --> 00:18:17,952
[speaking Korean]

331
00:18:21,414 --> 00:18:25,334
He wishes to speak
with your chairman directly.

332
00:18:25,418 --> 00:18:27,044
No, what'd he say before that?

333
00:18:28,003 --> 00:18:29,922
[Gyuseok speaking Korean]

334
00:18:31,298 --> 00:18:34,301
[speaking Korean]

335
00:18:37,012 --> 00:18:40,975
[speaking Korean]

336
00:18:41,851 --> 00:18:43,102
[speaking Korean]

337
00:18:43,185 --> 00:18:46,188
[speaking Korean]

338
00:18:50,985 --> 00:18:52,653
[Woojin] The chairman says,

339
00:18:52,737 --> 00:18:55,573
"The coffin in Korea's
now your responsibility.

340
00:18:55,656 --> 00:18:58,534
So you will have to move it yourself."

341
00:18:58,617 --> 00:19:00,870
[speaking Korean]

342
00:19:18,888 --> 00:19:20,389
[chopsticks clatter on plate]

343
00:19:38,324 --> 00:19:40,993
Something like this
isn't complete without a drink.

344
00:19:43,037 --> 00:19:44,038
My chairman told me...

345
00:19:45,289 --> 00:19:47,166
...to take extra special care of you.

346
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:50,711
He's committing everything
to this deal.

347
00:19:52,379 --> 00:19:54,048
[Woojin speaking Korean]

348
00:19:54,131 --> 00:19:57,009
[speaking Korean]

349
00:19:57,092 --> 00:20:01,138
[Woojin speaking Korean]

350
00:20:01,222 --> 00:20:02,515
[exhales sharply]

351
00:20:03,724 --> 00:20:04,975
[speaking Korean]

352
00:20:15,069 --> 00:20:16,070
How's it goin'?

353
00:20:17,321 --> 00:20:18,489
Dokyung hasn't opened his mouth yet?

354
00:20:18,572 --> 00:20:19,782
[snaps fingers]

355
00:20:21,575 --> 00:20:22,993
[Hocheol] I'm sorry.

356
00:20:23,077 --> 00:20:24,328
[Gyuseok] Hocheol, come on.

357
00:20:26,247 --> 00:20:27,414
[lighter flicks]

358
00:20:28,207 --> 00:20:29,625
Didn't you tell me not to worry?

359
00:20:30,376 --> 00:20:33,420
You said that bastard has nowhere to run
and that he's in your hands.

360
00:20:33,504 --> 00:20:35,005
[Gyuseok] So what now?

361
00:20:35,631 --> 00:20:39,385
[Hocheol] I'll go to the hospital myself,
then I'll shut him up.

362
00:20:39,468 --> 00:20:42,179
[Gyuseok] How, exactly?
You said the cops are involved.

363
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:45,641
[Hocheol] I know a detective at
the Gangwon Central Police Department.

364
00:20:46,851 --> 00:20:50,813
I might need to buy a little time
to have a moment alone with Dokyung.

365
00:20:50,896 --> 00:20:52,273
[Gyuseok] And what
if he still doesn't talk?

366
00:20:52,356 --> 00:20:53,566
Kill him?

367
00:20:54,441 --> 00:20:55,818
How would we find the casket?

368
00:20:55,901 --> 00:20:57,027
[Hocheol] Worst-case scenario.

369
00:20:57,111 --> 00:21:00,990
Even if we have to give up the casket,
shutting him up is the priority.

370
00:21:03,450 --> 00:21:05,077
Ah.

371
00:21:06,829 --> 00:21:08,247
Is that right?

372
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:10,040
That's the priority?

373
00:21:10,124 --> 00:21:12,126
[Gyuseok] I didn't realize that.

374
00:21:14,837 --> 00:21:15,838
Hey, Hocheol.

375
00:21:15,921 --> 00:21:17,715
[cigarette hissing]
STYLE
::cue()

376
00:21:18,924 --> 00:21:20,593
Are you the boss now?

377
00:21:20,676 --> 00:21:22,845
[Gyuseok] Do you get
to decide what's important?

378
00:21:25,139 --> 00:21:26,640
I'm sorry.

379
00:21:27,474 --> 00:21:29,435
I spoke out of turn.

380
00:21:29,518 --> 00:21:32,187
[Gyuseok] This bastard Lee Dokyung,
he married?

381
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:34,982
As far as I know,
he's not married.

382
00:21:35,065 --> 00:21:36,233
Hocheol, listen.

383
00:21:36,317 --> 00:21:38,319
Cut off a finger from a friend
or a bitch close to him

384
00:21:38,402 --> 00:21:39,653
and send it to him.

385
00:21:39,737 --> 00:21:40,821
You think he won't talk after that?

386
00:21:40,905 --> 00:21:43,032
Yes, I'll get on that right away.

387
00:21:43,949 --> 00:21:46,619
When you find the casket,
don't open it right away.

388
00:21:47,912 --> 00:21:49,663
Give me a call first.

389
00:21:49,747 --> 00:21:51,373
I want to go check it myself.

390
00:21:52,583 --> 00:21:53,584
[Hocheol] Yes, sir.

391
00:21:56,045 --> 00:21:58,130
Hocheol, make sure you get this right.

392
00:21:58,213 --> 00:21:59,340
[exhales]

393
00:21:59,423 --> 00:22:01,550
[Gyuseok] That casket better be sitting in

394
00:22:01,634 --> 00:22:03,928
the hotel before I get back
from this trip.

395
00:22:04,011 --> 00:22:05,012
Understand?

396
00:22:07,389 --> 00:22:08,641
Right.

397
00:22:08,724 --> 00:22:09,934
But sir.

398
00:22:10,809 --> 00:22:11,810
That cask-

399
00:22:11,894 --> 00:22:12,895
[phone beeps]

400
00:22:12,978 --> 00:22:15,981
[♪ suspenseful music]

401
00:22:22,363 --> 00:22:25,991
AHN GYUSEOK

402
00:22:44,134 --> 00:22:46,971
[door opens and closes]

403
00:22:47,054 --> 00:22:49,264
FIELD INVESTIGATION REPORT

404
00:22:49,348 --> 00:22:51,183
[Jinman] So it turns out the window on
the driver's side

405
00:22:51,266 --> 00:22:53,310
of the van was slightly open.

406
00:22:53,394 --> 00:22:57,231
It's lucky I caught that,
which is pretty genius, don't you think?

407
00:22:57,314 --> 00:22:58,524
Yeah?

408
00:22:58,607 --> 00:22:59,900
It's pretty dark,
but take a look.

409
00:23:01,068 --> 00:23:02,069
[Jinman] You see it?

410
00:23:02,152 --> 00:23:03,070
[Jinman] Can you make it out?

411
00:23:03,988 --> 00:23:05,698
See? It's a woman.

412
00:23:06,865 --> 00:23:08,450
[Jinman] And out of all
the witnesses involved in

413
00:23:08,534 --> 00:23:10,828
the smuggling case who were questioned by
the police,

414
00:23:10,911 --> 00:23:15,416
there was only one woman who had been
on National Route 6 that day.

415
00:23:15,499 --> 00:23:18,252
And even better,
she was caught by surveillance cameras.

416
00:23:19,086 --> 00:23:20,671
All right, so who is she?

417
00:23:20,754 --> 00:23:22,297
I can let you know soon.

418
00:23:22,381 --> 00:23:23,841
I'll even find that casket, too.

419
00:23:23,924 --> 00:23:28,012
[Jinman] I just don't have
any hard evidence yet. Okay?

420
00:23:28,095 --> 00:23:29,763
I don't wanna cause problems
by barking up the wrong tree.

421
00:23:29,847 --> 00:23:31,348
[Hocheol] Hard evidence?

422
00:23:32,349 --> 00:23:35,477
It's not like we're running
a police investigation here.

423
00:23:35,561 --> 00:23:37,938
Maybe, but I'm still a cop, aren't I?

424
00:23:38,022 --> 00:23:40,065
Cut the crap and tell me who
the woman is now.

425
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,401
[scoffs]

426
00:23:43,152 --> 00:23:44,153
Here.

427
00:23:45,779 --> 00:23:47,031
[clears throat]

428
00:23:50,659 --> 00:23:52,786
[Jinman] Head of Gangwon Security,
Cha Yujin.

429
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:55,289
[Jinman] There's a good chance
she's Lee Dokyung's accomplice.

430
00:23:55,372 --> 00:23:57,374
I already planted a tracking device
on her car,

431
00:23:57,458 --> 00:23:59,501
so don't worry about that, 'kay?

432
00:23:59,585 --> 00:24:02,504
Once they head to Jeongsan,
we just follow 'em. Simple.

433
00:24:02,588 --> 00:24:04,882
When?

434
00:24:04,965 --> 00:24:06,133
She'll go sooner or later.

435
00:24:06,216 --> 00:24:08,427
She has to.
The casket's there.

436
00:24:10,262 --> 00:24:11,430
'Kay, good work.

437
00:24:11,513 --> 00:24:14,433
Do you wanna be paid in cash,
or do you want chips?

438
00:24:14,516 --> 00:24:16,185
I'll take chips.

439
00:24:16,268 --> 00:24:18,979
I'll have a table set up tomorrow.
Just use 100.

440
00:24:19,063 --> 00:24:21,648
But I haven't found the casket yet.

441
00:24:21,732 --> 00:24:24,443
That's enough for now.
I'll take care of the rest.

442
00:24:27,029 --> 00:24:28,030
Ah.

443
00:24:29,948 --> 00:24:31,283
Don't mention the gold.

444
00:24:32,409 --> 00:24:35,037
We should pretend we don't know.
Even around the chairman.

445
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,082
[Hocheol] Actually, you know what?
Now that I think about it...

446
00:24:39,166 --> 00:24:41,627
...if the chairman were to find out you
and I know about the gold...

447
00:24:43,545 --> 00:24:45,089
...well, who knows what could happen?

448
00:24:45,172 --> 00:24:47,174
[Hocheol] I'm sure he didn't tell us
for a reason.

449
00:24:47,257 --> 00:24:50,135
Is that right?
So that's how it's gonna go.

450
00:24:52,096 --> 00:24:54,765
I guess that's how it is, then. Wow.

451
00:24:54,848 --> 00:24:56,308
[Jinman] Knowing Chairman Ahn,

452
00:24:56,391 --> 00:24:58,936
it couldn't have been easy
trusting someone with all that gold.

453
00:24:59,895 --> 00:25:00,896
[Jinman] Even if they were family.

454
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,607
[Jinman] That's hard to do. Yeah.

455
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:08,362
What if they see all that gold
and just totally lose their mind?

456
00:25:08,445 --> 00:25:11,031
[Jinman] Right? They could do
something crazy.

457
00:25:11,115 --> 00:25:13,575
That's why you told me to lay off.
Isn't that right?

458
00:25:13,659 --> 00:25:14,660
That's gotta be it.
STYLE
::cue()

459
00:25:17,788 --> 00:25:21,458
[sirens blaring]

460
00:25:21,542 --> 00:25:24,545
WARD 32

461
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:27,589
[snapping fingers]

462
00:25:30,843 --> 00:25:33,178
Lee Dokyung.
When's he getting transferred?

463
00:25:33,262 --> 00:25:34,263
[exhales]

464
00:25:34,972 --> 00:25:36,098
Monday.

465
00:25:37,307 --> 00:25:38,559
Let me see him real quick.

466
00:25:39,226 --> 00:25:42,229
Well, unless you registered in advance,
I can't-

467
00:25:42,312 --> 00:25:43,438
Five minutes.

468
00:25:45,023 --> 00:25:46,024
[Kang groans]

469
00:25:46,859 --> 00:25:48,277
Five minutes.
I mean it.

470
00:25:51,864 --> 00:25:52,948
Okay.

471
00:26:05,085 --> 00:26:07,004
[Hocheol] No, no, no, no, no, no.
Sit down, sit down, sit down.

472
00:26:07,087 --> 00:26:08,088
I'm just here to talk.

473
00:26:09,673 --> 00:26:13,177
I promised Detective Kang I wouldn't
be more than five minutes.

474
00:26:14,428 --> 00:26:16,221
[exhales]

475
00:26:16,305 --> 00:26:18,891
[Hocheol] Looks like you're on the mend.
You're up and walking.

476
00:26:19,808 --> 00:26:20,809
How's your head?

477
00:26:21,351 --> 00:26:22,352
Is it okay?

478
00:26:22,436 --> 00:26:24,229
Like I've said before.

479
00:26:25,105 --> 00:26:27,191
Unless my money and my safety
are guaranteed...

480
00:26:28,150 --> 00:26:29,985
I won't be telling you anything.

481
00:26:31,737 --> 00:26:33,697
[inhales]

482
00:26:34,656 --> 00:26:36,200
Do you even know what's inside the casket?

483
00:26:37,159 --> 00:26:38,202
[Hocheol] You do, don't you?

484
00:26:39,077 --> 00:26:40,704
[Hocheol] Maybe you knew from the start.

485
00:26:40,787 --> 00:26:42,789
Or maybe your accomplice told you later.

486
00:26:44,458 --> 00:26:46,335
[Hocheol] It doesn't matter either way.

487
00:26:46,418 --> 00:26:47,836
I know why you're holding out.

488
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:52,716
I wouldn't have said anything, either.

489
00:26:52,799 --> 00:26:55,302
[Hocheol] If I had a whole ton
of gold in my hands?

490
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,472
I'd go all in.
I mean, what else is there?

491
00:26:58,555 --> 00:27:02,601
[laughing]

492
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:06,772
I did some digging.

493
00:27:08,190 --> 00:27:11,610
It turns out your accomplice
was a woman.

494
00:27:14,905 --> 00:27:18,242
She works at the airport.
Yangpo, right?

495
00:27:18,325 --> 00:27:19,576
[Hocheol inhales sharply]

496
00:27:19,660 --> 00:27:20,869
[Hocheol] What's her name?

497
00:27:22,454 --> 00:27:23,622
Cha Yujin?

498
00:27:25,123 --> 00:27:26,583
[Hocheol] Your girlfriend.

499
00:27:26,667 --> 00:27:28,710
[Hocheol] I was thinking I should stop by
and meet her.

500
00:27:29,419 --> 00:27:31,129
[Hocheol] But if you don't
wanna make things messy,

501
00:27:31,213 --> 00:27:32,297
you should tell me what you know.

502
00:27:35,092 --> 00:27:36,969
Where's the casket?

503
00:27:38,762 --> 00:27:39,930
[light shuddering]

504
00:27:40,806 --> 00:27:42,307
I don't know where it is.

505
00:27:42,391 --> 00:27:44,226
Does Ms. Cha Yujin?

506
00:27:44,309 --> 00:27:46,937
It's not her.
She's got nothing to do with this.

507
00:27:48,021 --> 00:27:49,189
What are you getting at?

508
00:27:49,272 --> 00:27:50,315
She's not my girlfriend,

509
00:27:50,399 --> 00:27:52,025
and she doesn't know anything about
the casket.

510
00:27:52,109 --> 00:27:53,360
Then who does know?

511
00:27:53,902 --> 00:27:55,028
[sharp breathing]

512
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,615
[exhales]

513
00:28:00,993 --> 00:28:01,994
[Hocheol] The thing is...

514
00:28:02,995 --> 00:28:04,121
...I don't have time for this.

515
00:28:07,207 --> 00:28:09,835
By the end of this week,
I have to find that casket.

516
00:28:09,918 --> 00:28:11,253
I don't care what it takes.

517
00:28:15,090 --> 00:28:16,883
So I was thinking about
this whole thing...

518
00:28:18,802 --> 00:28:20,345
...when I suddenly realized...

519
00:28:23,390 --> 00:28:25,559
...why even bother finding
your accomplice?

520
00:28:26,643 --> 00:28:27,769
She won't admit to anything.

521
00:28:27,853 --> 00:28:29,146
[laughs]

522
00:28:30,272 --> 00:28:31,356
Then you know what I thought?

523
00:28:33,358 --> 00:28:34,401
I should just kill them all.

524
00:28:35,444 --> 00:28:37,529
[Hocheol] Every single woman connected
to you.

525
00:28:38,447 --> 00:28:39,448
One...

526
00:28:40,407 --> 00:28:42,159
...after another.

527
00:28:43,994 --> 00:28:45,787
Girlfriend or not.

528
00:28:47,122 --> 00:28:49,958
[Hocheol] Whether she stole
the casket or not.

529
00:28:51,293 --> 00:28:53,003
Until you open up.

530
00:28:54,004 --> 00:28:55,005
You understand?

531
00:28:59,926 --> 00:29:02,345
[Hocheol] You got till tomorrow
to think it over and let me know.

532
00:29:09,728 --> 00:29:11,855
If you don't talk,
I'm really gonna kill them all.

533
00:29:13,607 --> 00:29:15,859
Starting with your girlfriend.
STYLE
::cue()

534
00:29:15,942 --> 00:29:18,945
[shuddering]

535
00:29:24,534 --> 00:29:27,454
[door slides open and closed]

536
00:29:32,918 --> 00:29:36,421
[machines quietly beeping]

537
00:29:41,843 --> 00:29:43,303
[Heeju exhales]

538
00:29:56,358 --> 00:29:58,151
[grunts]

539
00:30:03,532 --> 00:30:06,535
[indistinct chatter]

540
00:30:10,413 --> 00:30:11,665
[Jinman coughs]

541
00:30:17,212 --> 00:30:20,257
[cell phone vibrates]

542
00:30:22,384 --> 00:30:24,136
[phone trilling]

543
00:30:25,178 --> 00:30:26,888
[phone vibrating]

544
00:30:26,972 --> 00:30:28,515
-[Jinman] Hello?
-Hello?

545
00:30:28,598 --> 00:30:29,808
-[Jinman] Hello? Ms. Kim?

546
00:30:29,891 --> 00:30:31,351
[Hospital Announcer]
Patient is in the ward...

547
00:30:31,434 --> 00:30:32,978
-Are you there?
-[Heeju] I'm sorry I'm not available.

548
00:30:33,061 --> 00:30:35,897
Leave a message and I'll call you back.
Have a good day. Bye.

549
00:30:36,815 --> 00:30:38,108
[Hospital Announcer]
Patient is in the ward.

550
00:30:38,191 --> 00:30:42,404
The guardian of patient Kim Minseo,
please go to the reception desk.

551
00:30:51,413 --> 00:30:53,039
[door clangs and creaks]

552
00:31:09,347 --> 00:31:10,390
[exhales sharply]

553
00:31:12,934 --> 00:31:15,896
What were you doing here?

554
00:31:16,897 --> 00:31:18,023
Oh, not you.

555
00:31:20,317 --> 00:31:23,695
[car engines revving]

556
00:31:23,778 --> 00:31:26,781
[cell phone vibrating]

557
00:31:30,785 --> 00:31:33,205
-Hello?
-[Dokyung] It's me, Dokyung.

558
00:31:33,288 --> 00:31:34,539
[inhales]

559
00:31:35,332 --> 00:31:36,666
One moment.

560
00:31:43,423 --> 00:31:45,008
[Yujin] Are you still in the hospital?

561
00:31:45,091 --> 00:31:46,343
[Dokyung] Yeah.

562
00:31:47,219 --> 00:31:48,720
[Yujin] Are you crazy?

563
00:31:48,803 --> 00:31:50,013
Why are you calling me?

564
00:31:51,014 --> 00:31:52,641
[Dokyung] Take some time off work.

565
00:31:52,724 --> 00:31:54,392
[Dokyung] And go overseas for a while.

566
00:31:54,476 --> 00:31:55,602
Why should I?

567
00:31:56,311 --> 00:31:57,896
Is it the casket?

568
00:31:57,979 --> 00:31:59,522
[Dokyung] You're in serious danger.

569
00:31:59,606 --> 00:32:01,566
You need to get out
of the country right now.

570
00:32:05,570 --> 00:32:06,780
Fine.

571
00:32:06,863 --> 00:32:09,574
[Yujin] But first,
let me just ask you one thing.

572
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:12,786
No one's listening in on our call, right?

573
00:32:13,954 --> 00:32:15,747
No.

574
00:32:16,873 --> 00:32:19,209
What on earth is inside of that casket?

575
00:32:22,254 --> 00:32:23,964
If it's too difficult
for you to say out loud,

576
00:32:24,047 --> 00:32:27,008
just answer my questions.
It's not drugs, right?

577
00:32:27,092 --> 00:32:28,385
[Dokyung] It's not.

578
00:32:28,468 --> 00:32:30,095
Is it gold?

579
00:32:31,638 --> 00:32:33,723
[Yujin] The X-ray picked up
a high-density material,

580
00:32:33,807 --> 00:32:35,267
like metal.

581
00:32:35,350 --> 00:32:37,602
No mechanical parts,
like with firearms,

582
00:32:37,686 --> 00:32:41,314
but more like solid masses of metal
with no impurities.

583
00:32:41,398 --> 00:32:43,608
[Yujin] But you wouldn't have brought
in something like iron.

584
00:32:46,611 --> 00:32:48,196
Just tell me the truth.

585
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,407
I promise I'll leave
the country like you said.

586
00:32:56,329 --> 00:32:57,330
[Yujin] Fine, then.

587
00:32:57,956 --> 00:32:59,040
[phone beeps]

588
00:32:59,124 --> 00:33:00,208
[exhales]
STYLE
::cue()

589
00:33:14,139 --> 00:33:15,140
[car alarm beeps]

590
00:33:15,223 --> 00:33:18,226
[indistinct chatter]

591
00:33:18,601 --> 00:33:21,146
TEMPORARILY CLOSED
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

592
00:33:21,229 --> 00:33:24,232
[gate clanging]

593
00:33:26,693 --> 00:33:28,361
[keys jangling]

594
00:33:28,445 --> 00:33:29,612
[exhales]

595
00:33:36,411 --> 00:33:38,496
[Heeju] Shit.

596
00:33:40,248 --> 00:33:42,167
[panicked breathing]

597
00:33:48,506 --> 00:33:52,677
[cell phone vibrates]

598
00:33:52,761 --> 00:33:55,180
TEAM LEADER CHA YUJIN

599
00:33:57,015 --> 00:33:58,016
[phone clicks]

600
00:34:03,021 --> 00:34:04,731
[phone buzzes rapidly]

601
00:34:05,690 --> 00:34:06,775
[exhales]

602
00:34:08,651 --> 00:34:09,903
[Yujin] If you don't call me,

603
00:34:09,986 --> 00:34:11,696
I'll tell the police
that you're in Jeongsan.

604
00:34:16,743 --> 00:34:19,996
[cell phone vibrating]

605
00:34:34,260 --> 00:34:35,345
Hello?

606
00:34:38,056 --> 00:34:39,349
Is this how I get you to call?

607
00:34:39,432 --> 00:34:41,226
[Yujin] Are you avoiding me?

608
00:34:41,309 --> 00:34:43,395
Uh, no, not at all.

609
00:34:43,478 --> 00:34:45,313
[Yujin] I'm on my way to Jeongsan now
to see you.

610
00:34:47,982 --> 00:34:48,983
Why?

611
00:34:49,067 --> 00:34:50,527
[Yujin] It must be hard on you,

612
00:34:50,610 --> 00:34:52,570
considering what's inside that casket.

613
00:34:52,654 --> 00:34:54,447
I can help you.

614
00:34:56,491 --> 00:34:59,327
Really?
So what's inside of it?

615
00:34:59,411 --> 00:35:01,454
[Yujin] You know very well
what's inside it.

616
00:35:02,497 --> 00:35:05,041
I'll call you when I get there.
Let's have a drink somewhere quiet.

617
00:35:15,301 --> 00:35:18,638
[Heeju] Now there was one more person
besides Woogy.

618
00:35:18,722 --> 00:35:21,975
One more person who knew I
had the gold bars.

619
00:35:22,976 --> 00:35:26,563
I need to find out how much she know.

620
00:35:26,646 --> 00:35:29,774
[clocks ticking]

621
00:35:29,858 --> 00:35:32,777
[♪ lively music playing]

622
00:35:32,861 --> 00:35:35,864
[indistinct lively chatter]

623
00:35:45,582 --> 00:35:48,126
[Yujin] Hi! You're here!

624
00:35:51,045 --> 00:35:52,297
[Yujin] Whoo, whoo!

625
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:53,715
Whoo!

626
00:35:54,591 --> 00:35:56,926
[Yujin] Hurry up! Hi!

627
00:35:59,345 --> 00:36:00,764
[Yujin] You didn't bring your car,
did you?

628
00:36:00,847 --> 00:36:02,557
Let's drink till we drop.

629
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,392
No, I drove here.

630
00:36:04,476 --> 00:36:06,186
Why? That's no fun.

631
00:36:08,146 --> 00:36:10,064
You said you wanted
to talk someplace quiet.

632
00:36:10,148 --> 00:36:13,860
I did. It's better to have quiet convos
in loud places.

633
00:36:14,861 --> 00:36:17,614
All right, go ahead, then.
I can't be gone long.

634
00:36:18,740 --> 00:36:19,991
Come on.

635
00:36:20,492 --> 00:36:22,702
Sweetie, why are you so grumpy?

636
00:36:22,786 --> 00:36:24,662
[Yujin] Keep this up
and you'll hurt my feelings.

637
00:36:25,622 --> 00:36:26,873
[Yujin] The thing is...

638
00:36:28,166 --> 00:36:31,377
...I spoke with Dokyung on
the phone before I came here.

639
00:36:31,461 --> 00:36:32,879
The casket.

640
00:36:34,547 --> 00:36:37,217
[Yujin] He asked me to help you get
it out of the country.

641
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:39,344
And he even told me what's inside of it.

642
00:36:40,762 --> 00:36:42,555
What's inside of it, then?

643
00:36:44,557 --> 00:36:45,892
Gold bars.

644
00:36:48,228 --> 00:36:49,354
[Yujin exhales]

645
00:36:49,437 --> 00:36:51,689
[Yujin] But don't take it the wrong way.

646
00:36:51,773 --> 00:36:55,068
I guess he just thought I
was more reliable than you

647
00:36:55,151 --> 00:36:56,444
when it came to moving them.

648
00:36:57,487 --> 00:36:59,405
So where's the casket now?

649
00:37:03,660 --> 00:37:05,328
I guess he didn't tell you that part.

650
00:37:05,411 --> 00:37:07,038
Mm-hmm.

651
00:37:07,121 --> 00:37:09,207
'Cause he told me I should just ask you.

652
00:37:10,208 --> 00:37:11,376
[exhales]

653
00:37:11,459 --> 00:37:13,253
You're lying to me.

654
00:37:13,336 --> 00:37:15,505
He would never tell you about
the gold bars.

655
00:37:16,506 --> 00:37:17,799
He really did, though.

656
00:37:20,844 --> 00:37:24,514
[Yujin] But that's not important.
You really are naive.

657
00:37:24,597 --> 00:37:28,434
It really doesn't matter who Dokyung loves
or whether you believe me
STYLE
::cue()

658
00:37:28,518 --> 00:37:30,270
or don't believe me.
None of it matters.

659
00:37:30,353 --> 00:37:33,356
[Yujin] If he gets his hands on
the gold bars,

660
00:37:33,439 --> 00:37:34,440
the outcome is the same for us.

661
00:37:35,942 --> 00:37:37,068
It's Lee Dokyung.

662
00:37:37,151 --> 00:37:40,989
He's not gonna share it with you
or me or any other woman.

663
00:37:46,578 --> 00:37:48,162
I have Cha Yujin's location.

664
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:50,707
Yes, in Jeongsan.

665
00:37:51,291 --> 00:37:54,294
Yeah. Yeah, the club in front
of Gold Land.

666
00:37:55,253 --> 00:37:57,171
[Jinman] But I have no idea
if she's still there or not.

667
00:37:57,714 --> 00:37:59,465
'Kay, good work.

668
00:37:59,549 --> 00:38:00,717
[phone beeps]

669
00:38:02,093 --> 00:38:04,220
That asshole has no fucking manners.

670
00:38:05,597 --> 00:38:07,140
It's Jeongsan.

671
00:38:07,223 --> 00:38:08,558
Jeongsan Hobak Nightclub.

672
00:38:08,641 --> 00:38:10,018
Are you saying she's here in town?

673
00:38:10,101 --> 00:38:11,644
She's probably looking
for the casket.

674
00:38:12,687 --> 00:38:15,023
Share Cha Yujin's photo.
Call the boys.

675
00:38:15,106 --> 00:38:16,274
Don't just sit there!

676
00:38:16,357 --> 00:38:18,693
[nervous breathing]

677
00:38:18,776 --> 00:38:19,986
[Hocheol] Hey!

678
00:38:20,069 --> 00:38:22,071
Do it right!

679
00:38:22,155 --> 00:38:24,532
If anyone loses her, I swear
I'll cut off one of their fucking ears.

680
00:38:24,616 --> 00:38:25,909
Okay.

681
00:38:27,577 --> 00:38:28,870
[cell phone vibrating]

682
00:38:32,290 --> 00:38:34,626
SENT A PHOTO: PRESIDENT KO

683
00:38:34,709 --> 00:38:37,378
[Gitae] Meet up at Jeongsan
Hobak Nightclub. Find this woman.

684
00:38:42,842 --> 00:38:44,844
[cell phone beeps]

685
00:38:44,928 --> 00:38:48,598
[phone trilling]

686
00:38:49,766 --> 00:38:52,477
[motorcycle engine revving]

687
00:38:56,439 --> 00:38:58,358
[Yujin] As of right now,

688
00:38:58,441 --> 00:39:01,903
the police suspect
I'm Dokyung's accomplice.

689
00:39:01,986 --> 00:39:06,324
And I'm pretending I don't know anything
since it's currently better that way.

690
00:39:08,159 --> 00:39:11,204
I don't know how much longer
I can keep this up, though.

691
00:39:12,121 --> 00:39:14,958
[Yujin] Honestly, there's no reason
for me to get on the suspect list just

692
00:39:15,041 --> 00:39:16,292
to protect you.

693
00:39:20,129 --> 00:39:22,590
You want the gold.
Is that what it is?

694
00:39:22,674 --> 00:39:24,467
Mm-hmm.

695
00:39:26,844 --> 00:39:29,681
You got it. Bingo.

696
00:39:31,307 --> 00:39:32,892
The deal will be different.

697
00:39:34,268 --> 00:39:35,311
You know what I think?

698
00:39:35,395 --> 00:39:37,730
We should just split it between
the two of us.

699
00:39:38,398 --> 00:39:39,857
Hear me out.

700
00:39:39,941 --> 00:39:41,859
[Yujin] You're the one holding all
the cards right now.

701
00:39:41,943 --> 00:39:45,613
And since you are,
you get to call the shots.

702
00:39:46,781 --> 00:39:49,617
Do you wanna hand everything over
to Lee Dokyung?

703
00:39:49,701 --> 00:39:52,203
[Yujin] Or do you wanna split
it fifty-fifty with me?

704
00:39:53,121 --> 00:39:58,334
[Yujin exhales]

705
00:39:58,418 --> 00:40:01,212
[Yujin] Look, there's only one way
this'll end if you go it alone.

706
00:40:01,295 --> 00:40:04,257
What'll you do?
Hold onto the gold for months?

707
00:40:05,758 --> 00:40:09,178
All the cops already know the casket
is right here in Jeongsan.

708
00:40:09,262 --> 00:40:10,596
And even if you were lucky enough

709
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:13,683
to hold onto the gold all that time,
then what?

710
00:40:13,766 --> 00:40:17,687
The second Lee Dokyung gets out,
he's gonna take it all away from you.

711
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:19,814
Even though you were
the one who did all the work.

712
00:40:22,775 --> 00:40:23,943
Here's what I think.

713
00:40:26,654 --> 00:40:28,072
[Yujin] We have no choice.

714
00:40:28,156 --> 00:40:30,074
We have to get that casket out of here.

715
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:32,201
Overseas.

716
00:40:33,161 --> 00:40:36,539
The same way it was brought in through
the airport in the first place.

717
00:40:36,622 --> 00:40:40,418
And can you think of anyone else who
could pull that off better than me?

718
00:40:43,838 --> 00:40:45,757
[Male Waiter] All right.

719
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:48,176
Here's the fruit platter. And...

720
00:40:49,093 --> 00:40:51,054
...this one's on the house.

721
00:40:51,137 --> 00:40:52,847
Have a fun night.

722
00:40:56,100 --> 00:40:57,351
[indistinct lively chatter]

723
00:40:57,435 --> 00:41:00,188
[♪ lively club music playing]

724
00:41:00,271 --> 00:41:02,106
[drink sizzling]

725
00:41:05,985 --> 00:41:07,195
You wanna try?

726
00:41:07,278 --> 00:41:09,447
Oh, this?

727
00:41:10,490 --> 00:41:12,950
I heard this is what
the kids call Rainbow.

728
00:41:14,202 --> 00:41:16,496
'Cause it makes you feel great
when you take it.

729
00:41:27,215 --> 00:41:29,050
Why don't you think it over some more?

730
00:41:29,133 --> 00:41:30,510
I'm gonna go have fun.

731
00:41:36,265 --> 00:41:37,350
[Heeju exhales sharply]
STYLE
::cue()

732
00:41:39,018 --> 00:41:40,812
HOBAK, ADULT-ONLY ENTERTAINMENT
NIGHTCLUB

733
00:41:42,730 --> 00:41:45,066
[Club Guard] Evening.
Welcome in.

734
00:41:49,153 --> 00:41:50,446
-[Gitae] Hey, Moonsu!
-[Moonsu] Yes, sir.

735
00:41:50,530 --> 00:41:51,781
[Gitae] Stand guard at the back door.

736
00:41:51,864 --> 00:41:53,032
-[Moonsu] Yes, boss.
-[Gitae] Okay.

737
00:41:53,116 --> 00:41:54,117
[Gitae] Stay sharp, everyone!

738
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,201
[All] Yes, sir!

739
00:42:00,164 --> 00:42:02,834
[crowd cheering]

740
00:42:02,917 --> 00:42:05,920
[♪ loud club music playing]

741
00:42:07,672 --> 00:42:09,382
[cell phone vibrates]

742
00:42:14,345 --> 00:42:15,721
MISSED CALL
WOOGY

743
00:42:16,806 --> 00:42:18,850
[Woogy] Isn't this your boss?

744
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:25,857
[Clubgoer A] Oh, move, move. Oh.

745
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:28,192
-[Clubgoer B] What's going on?
-[Clubgoer B] Stay away from them.

746
00:42:28,276 --> 00:42:29,569
[Clubgoer A] Stay out of their way.

747
00:42:31,154 --> 00:42:32,822
[Gitae] Hey, you all have the photo,
right?

748
00:42:32,905 --> 00:42:35,116
-[All] Yes, sir!
-[Gitae] Okay. Spread out and find her.

749
00:42:35,199 --> 00:42:36,576
[Henchman] Yes, sir!

750
00:42:36,659 --> 00:42:38,077
[Gitae] Hold up. You two wait here.

751
00:42:38,161 --> 00:42:39,412
[Both] Yes, sir.

752
00:42:39,495 --> 00:42:40,872
-[Gitae] And you!
-[Clubgoer A] Come on, come on.

753
00:42:40,955 --> 00:42:42,165
[Clubgoer A] We'll find another club.

754
00:42:43,875 --> 00:42:46,294
[panicked breathing]

755
00:42:46,377 --> 00:42:48,379
[cell phone chimes, trills]

756
00:42:50,756 --> 00:42:51,966
Hey, what's going on?

757
00:42:52,049 --> 00:42:53,634
Where'd you get that photo?

758
00:42:53,718 --> 00:42:55,803
Well, is it your boss or not?

759
00:42:56,387 --> 00:42:57,388
It's her, right?

760
00:42:58,264 --> 00:43:00,892
Seems my company is after her.
I hear she's in Jeongsan.

761
00:43:00,975 --> 00:43:03,311
What? Where in Jeongsan?

762
00:43:03,394 --> 00:43:05,229
[Woogy] Uh, Jeongsan Hobak Nightclub.

763
00:43:06,939 --> 00:43:09,609
Wait, where are you?
Why is it so loud?

764
00:43:10,484 --> 00:43:12,195
Hold on. Are you with her?

765
00:43:13,070 --> 00:43:15,114
You better get the fuck outta there!

766
00:43:15,198 --> 00:43:17,783
[indistinct chatter]

767
00:43:22,580 --> 00:43:24,373
[Woogy] I'm telling you, my company's
looking for her right now.

768
00:43:24,457 --> 00:43:26,500
If you stay there,
you're gonna get caught.

769
00:43:28,544 --> 00:43:29,837
Shit.

770
00:43:29,921 --> 00:43:30,922
[Woogy] I'm on my way to the workshop,
okay?

771
00:43:31,005 --> 00:43:33,257
You gotta just ditch her and get out.

772
00:43:39,722 --> 00:43:41,015
Are you there?

773
00:43:41,098 --> 00:43:42,099
Hello?

774
00:43:42,183 --> 00:43:43,184
Heeju.

775
00:43:44,644 --> 00:43:45,645
Hel-

776
00:43:47,521 --> 00:43:48,522
This is bad.

777
00:43:49,565 --> 00:43:52,568
[breathing erratically]

778
00:43:54,695 --> 00:43:58,115
[indistinct loud chatter]

779
00:44:06,791 --> 00:44:10,503
Excuse me. Excuse me, sorry.
Sorry. 'Scuse me.

780
00:44:10,586 --> 00:44:12,088
Ms. Cha, we have to leave now.

781
00:44:12,171 --> 00:44:14,882
-Wh-What? Why?
-They're here to get you.

782
00:44:14,966 --> 00:44:16,008
[Yujin] Who? Who's here?

783
00:44:16,926 --> 00:44:18,886
[Heeju] What do I do?
Ah, shoot.

784
00:44:18,970 --> 00:44:19,887
What?

785
00:44:19,971 --> 00:44:21,222
-[Hocheol] Where d'you think you're going?
-[Yujin] What's going on?

786
00:44:21,305 --> 00:44:23,099
-[Heeju] This way.
-[Gitae] Hold on a sec.

787
00:44:24,892 --> 00:44:27,353
Sorry. Sorry about that.

788
00:44:29,230 --> 00:44:30,231
Shit.

789
00:44:30,314 --> 00:44:31,607
He's gone.

790
00:44:35,528 --> 00:44:38,531
[both breathing heavily]

791
00:44:46,622 --> 00:44:48,374
[gate creaking]

792
00:44:50,459 --> 00:44:51,460
This way.

793
00:44:52,461 --> 00:44:54,297
[both breathing heavily]

794
00:44:54,380 --> 00:44:56,090
[Yujin] He's coming! Run!
Hurry, hurry!

795
00:44:57,633 --> 00:45:00,094
-[Heeju] Here, I think it's this way.
-[Jinman] Hey! Cha Yujin!

796
00:45:00,177 --> 00:45:02,179
[Yujin] Run! Run, he's coming!

797
00:45:02,263 --> 00:45:04,307
-[Heeju] Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah, keys.
-[Jinman] Hey! Hey!

798
00:45:04,390 --> 00:45:05,850
[Jinman] Cha Yujin!
STYLE
::cue()

799
00:45:05,933 --> 00:45:08,519
[Jinman] Wait! Cha Yujin!
Open the door!

800
00:45:08,602 --> 00:45:10,604
[Jinman] Hey!

801
00:45:10,688 --> 00:45:11,772
No, wait! Stop!

802
00:45:11,856 --> 00:45:14,275
-Stop! Hey!
-[Yujin] Drive! Drive!

803
00:45:14,358 --> 00:45:15,484
No!

804
00:45:15,568 --> 00:45:16,944
[car engine revving]

805
00:45:17,028 --> 00:45:18,154
[car horn honks]

806
00:45:18,237 --> 00:45:19,613
[breathing heavily]

807
00:45:20,656 --> 00:45:22,616
[Jinman] There's two of 'em?

808
00:45:22,700 --> 00:45:25,619
[labored breathing]

809
00:45:25,703 --> 00:45:28,873
[both breathing heavily]

810
00:45:28,956 --> 00:45:30,249
Ah, shit.

811
00:45:30,333 --> 00:45:32,376
[Yujin] How did they know where
to find us?

812
00:45:36,881 --> 00:45:39,216
-[Heeju] Ah, shit.
-Do you think they're cops or something?

813
00:45:41,510 --> 00:45:43,429
Those guys aren't detectives.

814
00:45:43,512 --> 00:45:45,056
Huh?

815
00:45:45,139 --> 00:45:47,808
They're from Yes Money,
a loan shark company around here.

816
00:45:48,476 --> 00:45:51,520
They're the ones who smuggled
the casket in.

817
00:45:51,604 --> 00:45:53,481
And Kim Jinman, the detective,

818
00:45:53,564 --> 00:45:54,982
this whole time he's been in on it, too.

819
00:45:56,650 --> 00:45:58,694
If we get caught by the cops,
we go to jail.

820
00:45:59,737 --> 00:46:01,906
We'll be out in a year or two.
But if we get caught by those guys...

821
00:46:04,492 --> 00:46:06,911
...the gold bars won't be
the only thing we lose.

822
00:46:06,994 --> 00:46:08,496
We'll both lose our lives.

823
00:46:08,579 --> 00:46:10,915
[Yujin] Shit, no wonder.

824
00:46:10,998 --> 00:46:12,875
There was something off about
that fucking detective.

825
00:46:14,627 --> 00:46:17,671
Oh, so that's why that asshole Dokyung
said I should leave the country.

826
00:46:18,672 --> 00:46:20,049
[exhales sharply]

827
00:46:21,300 --> 00:46:23,052
So what do we do now?

828
00:46:23,135 --> 00:46:25,971
We have to be smart.
There's no room for taking chances.

829
00:46:27,306 --> 00:46:29,975
Okay, sweetie.
You need to make a decision.

830
00:46:31,394 --> 00:46:32,478
Is it me or Dokyung?

831
00:46:32,561 --> 00:46:34,021
Does that really matter right now?

832
00:46:34,730 --> 00:46:36,899
If those guys back there catch us,
then we're dead.

833
00:46:36,982 --> 00:46:39,360
So what?
I'll die whenever I'm gonna die!

834
00:46:40,653 --> 00:46:41,946
Come on, sweetie.

835
00:46:42,613 --> 00:46:44,365
Let's go get the gold together.

836
00:46:45,157 --> 00:46:46,450
[groans]

837
00:46:55,709 --> 00:46:57,128
[tires squeak]

838
00:46:58,462 --> 00:47:01,465
[gate rattling]

839
00:47:03,050 --> 00:47:04,051
[keys jangle]

840
00:47:04,135 --> 00:47:05,344
[lock clicks]

841
00:47:05,428 --> 00:47:07,388
[door squeaks]

842
00:47:14,353 --> 00:47:16,063
[door creaking]

843
00:47:20,192 --> 00:47:21,235
Do you live here?

844
00:47:22,653 --> 00:47:24,989
-Well, for the time being.
-Oh.

845
00:47:30,536 --> 00:47:32,538
Didn't you say that you lived
with your aunt?

846
00:47:33,330 --> 00:47:34,623
She's in the hospital.

847
00:47:36,125 --> 00:47:37,501
[Yujin] Oh.

848
00:47:37,585 --> 00:47:39,211
So you're alone, then.

849
00:47:41,797 --> 00:47:43,716
You can stay here until it's light out.

850
00:47:43,799 --> 00:47:45,134
Sleep in that room over there.

851
00:47:46,177 --> 00:47:48,596
And I'll come back tomorrow.

852
00:47:49,930 --> 00:47:51,182
[Yujin] Why? Where are you going?

853
00:47:52,558 --> 00:47:53,642
To get the gold?

854
00:47:54,935 --> 00:47:55,936
[Heeju] Huh?

855
00:47:56,020 --> 00:47:58,814
[electric sizzling]

856
00:48:00,733 --> 00:48:01,734
[Heeju groans]

857
00:48:07,114 --> 00:48:08,491
[thuds]

858
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:10,493
[Yujin exhales]

859
00:48:11,827 --> 00:48:13,204
[chuckles]

860
00:48:19,043 --> 00:48:20,586
[deep exhale]

861
00:48:23,464 --> 00:48:26,467
[ticking clocks echoing]
STYLE
::cue()

862
00:48:30,679 --> 00:48:33,891
[Moonsu] Woogy, you asshole,
you didn't show. Where are you?

863
00:48:33,974 --> 00:48:36,435
[Woogy] I told you, I'm going to Daejeon
to get President Jo.

864
00:48:37,853 --> 00:48:38,854
Where are you?

865
00:48:39,772 --> 00:48:40,856
You nearby?

866
00:48:40,940 --> 00:48:43,859
Oh, yeah. That chick.
Were you able to get her?

867
00:48:43,943 --> 00:48:46,654
-Cha Yujin?
-[Moonsu] We fuckin' lost her.

868
00:48:46,737 --> 00:48:49,114
Look, the boss is here,
and he's really pissed off, too!

869
00:48:49,198 --> 00:48:50,824
Says he's gonna cut off everyone's ears,
man.

870
00:48:51,784 --> 00:48:53,035
That's her, right?

871
00:48:53,118 --> 00:48:55,329
The woman?
She stole the casket.

872
00:48:55,412 --> 00:48:57,623
-Dokyung's accomplice?
-[Moonsu] Of course she is!

873
00:48:57,706 --> 00:49:00,251
So finish up whatever you're doing
and get your ass over here.

874
00:49:00,334 --> 00:49:01,752
'Kay, I'll be there.

875
00:49:01,835 --> 00:49:04,046
[flames roaring]

876
00:49:04,129 --> 00:49:05,256
[phone beeps]

877
00:49:05,881 --> 00:49:07,007
Whew!

878
00:49:07,091 --> 00:49:08,425
Shit, that's lucky.

879
00:49:09,426 --> 00:49:10,469
CONNECTING CALL...
HEEJU

880
00:49:10,553 --> 00:49:13,556
[phone trilling]

881
00:49:21,730 --> 00:49:23,732
Ah, come on.
Why isn't she picking up?

882
00:49:23,816 --> 00:49:25,067
[phone beeps]

883
00:49:36,287 --> 00:49:39,290
[♪ suspenseful music]

884
00:49:41,542 --> 00:49:42,918
[exhales]

885
00:49:45,004 --> 00:49:48,007
[tires rumbling]

886
00:50:01,312 --> 00:50:02,813
[exhales]

887
00:50:02,896 --> 00:50:05,107
[muffled shouting]

888
00:50:05,190 --> 00:50:07,860
[cell phone vibrating]

889
00:50:14,074 --> 00:50:16,035
[phone buzzing]

890
00:50:25,669 --> 00:50:28,172
[Woogy] Hello? Uh, Heeju.
Where are you?

891
00:50:28,255 --> 00:50:30,132
-Why didn't you answer?
-[muffled shouting]

892
00:50:30,215 --> 00:50:31,342
You there?

893
00:50:31,425 --> 00:50:32,968
[Heeju shouting muffled]

894
00:50:33,052 --> 00:50:34,553
You hear me?

895
00:50:34,637 --> 00:50:36,930
I can't hear you.
What are you saying?

896
00:50:37,014 --> 00:50:38,849
[door opens]

897
00:50:38,932 --> 00:50:40,142
[Heeju grunts]

898
00:50:42,353 --> 00:50:43,937
[Yujin] Poor baby.

899
00:50:48,150 --> 00:50:50,110
You hid the gold bars in the mine,
didn't you?

900
00:50:51,362 --> 00:50:53,822
[Yujin] I saw coal caked all over
the car tires.

901
00:50:54,657 --> 00:50:55,699
[Yujin] Here.

902
00:50:55,783 --> 00:50:59,370
[Yujin] The coal mine at the end
of National Route 7, right?

903
00:50:59,453 --> 00:51:00,496
Inside the drift.

904
00:51:00,579 --> 00:51:02,331
[Yujin] Huh? Huh?

905
00:51:02,414 --> 00:51:04,500
-Right?
-Ms. Cha! Ms. Cha, wait!

906
00:51:04,583 --> 00:51:05,751
You won't find them on your own.

907
00:51:05,834 --> 00:51:07,336
I'm the only one who knows
exactly where they are.

908
00:51:07,419 --> 00:51:08,504
I'll go with you!

909
00:51:08,587 --> 00:51:11,674
[Heeju] We can go together
and split the gold bars, okay?

910
00:51:11,757 --> 00:51:13,384
Now you're saying that?

911
00:51:13,467 --> 00:51:16,220
[Yujin] Well, too late.
I don't need you.

912
00:51:16,303 --> 00:51:17,763
I'll look all night if I have to.

913
00:51:17,846 --> 00:51:19,598
I'll just use a metal detector
or something.

914
00:51:21,725 --> 00:51:23,352
You really are naive.

915
00:51:23,435 --> 00:51:25,813
Do you honestly think Lee Dokyung
and I keep you around

916
00:51:25,896 --> 00:51:27,439
because you actually matter?

917
00:51:27,523 --> 00:51:29,149
[Yujin] It's like I already told you.

918
00:51:29,233 --> 00:51:32,736
The only reason you were useful
was because of the gold.

919
00:51:32,820 --> 00:51:33,946
Not because we need you.

920
00:51:34,029 --> 00:51:35,239
-I beg you.
-[Yujin] Yeah?

921
00:51:35,322 --> 00:51:36,407
[gasps]

922
00:51:36,490 --> 00:51:38,367
[Heeju] Let's split them!

923
00:51:38,951 --> 00:51:41,578
[Heeju gasping]

924
00:51:41,662 --> 00:51:42,705
[Heeju wails]

925
00:51:42,788 --> 00:51:44,707
Please!

926
00:51:44,790 --> 00:51:46,583
[muffled shouting]

927
00:51:47,459 --> 00:51:51,547
[Yujin] You know, I was wondering what
to do with you.

928
00:51:51,630 --> 00:51:53,424
[Yujin] I was a bit conflicted.

929
00:51:53,507 --> 00:51:55,259
But you just helped me make up my mind.

930
00:51:56,427 --> 00:51:59,722
Yeah. Someone like you doesn't deserve
the gold.

931
00:51:59,805 --> 00:52:01,765
[muffled screaming]

932
00:52:01,849 --> 00:52:03,392
[door opens and closes]

933
00:52:04,977 --> 00:52:05,978
[car door beeps]

934
00:52:07,604 --> 00:52:09,064
[car engine turns over]

935
00:52:09,148 --> 00:52:10,774
[engine revving]

936
00:52:10,858 --> 00:52:13,068
[tires squeal]
STYLE
::cue()

937
00:52:14,486 --> 00:52:16,238
[Yujin] Just drink this
and never wake up.

938
00:52:17,781 --> 00:52:19,158
[Yujin] You think you're in love,
but the truth is,

939
00:52:19,241 --> 00:52:20,868
you're leeching off of Dokyung.

940
00:52:20,951 --> 00:52:23,120
And even after your life is wrecked,

941
00:52:23,203 --> 00:52:26,665
you still cry out,
"I was truly in love." Right?

942
00:52:26,749 --> 00:52:28,792
You've spent your whole life
telling yourself that.

943
00:52:28,876 --> 00:52:31,044
[Heeju whimpering]

944
00:52:31,128 --> 00:52:32,838
[Yujin] Sweetie.

945
00:52:33,756 --> 00:52:35,549
[Yujin] You really wanna go on
living like that?

946
00:52:35,632 --> 00:52:37,176
[Heeju groaning]

947
00:52:37,259 --> 00:52:38,719
Just die.

948
00:52:39,928 --> 00:52:42,931
[muffled shouting]

949
00:52:45,726 --> 00:52:47,269
[coughing]

950
00:52:47,352 --> 00:52:48,854
[bottle clatters]

951
00:52:48,937 --> 00:52:52,399
[both breathing heavily]

952
00:52:52,483 --> 00:52:54,359
Goodnight, sweetie.

953
00:52:54,443 --> 00:52:56,195
Forever.

954
00:52:56,278 --> 00:52:59,281
[♪ tense music]

955
00:53:02,701 --> 00:53:04,578
[coughing]

956
00:53:12,419 --> 00:53:15,589
[Heeju grunting]

957
00:53:20,803 --> 00:53:22,471
[muffled coughing]

958
00:53:39,071 --> 00:53:40,489
[lights buzzing loudly]

959
00:53:40,572 --> 00:53:43,283
[Heeju groaning]

960
00:54:07,266 --> 00:54:10,269
[grunting continues]

961
00:54:13,564 --> 00:54:16,567
[coughing]

962
00:54:20,988 --> 00:54:23,448
[gasping]

963
00:54:23,532 --> 00:54:26,493
[breathing heavily]

964
00:54:26,577 --> 00:54:29,246
[door creaking]

965
00:54:30,289 --> 00:54:33,292
[labored breathing]

966
00:54:40,132 --> 00:54:42,134
[coughing]

967
00:54:43,635 --> 00:54:46,638
[car approaching]

968
00:54:46,722 --> 00:54:47,931
[gags]

969
00:54:51,935 --> 00:54:53,562
[Woogy] Whoa! Heeju!

970
00:54:53,645 --> 00:54:54,896
You 'kay?

971
00:54:54,980 --> 00:54:56,273
Get up.

972
00:54:56,356 --> 00:54:57,858
You okay?

973
00:54:59,735 --> 00:55:00,902
Where're you going?

974
00:55:00,986 --> 00:55:01,987
[gasps]

975
00:55:02,070 --> 00:55:03,322
[Woogy] Huh?

976
00:55:04,114 --> 00:55:05,866
-I have to go.
-Where you tryin' to go?

977
00:55:05,949 --> 00:55:08,201
The mine?
Let's take my car.

978
00:55:08,744 --> 00:55:11,288
-You can't. Don't follow me.
-Ah, come here!

979
00:55:11,371 --> 00:55:14,374
[both grunting]

980
00:55:15,709 --> 00:55:17,544
-[Woogy] Okay.
-[Heeju] Cha Yujin.

981
00:55:17,628 --> 00:55:20,631
[both grunting]

982
00:55:23,383 --> 00:55:25,802
[gold bars clinking]

983
00:55:25,886 --> 00:55:27,638
[grunting]

984
00:55:38,815 --> 00:55:39,983
I heard everything on the call.

985
00:55:40,067 --> 00:55:41,985
That bitch, Cha Yujin.

986
00:55:42,694 --> 00:55:44,071
That woman really drugged
the fuck out of you.

987
00:55:44,154 --> 00:55:46,198
[Woogy] And she's heading to the mine
to steal the gold.

988
00:55:46,948 --> 00:55:48,033
Hurry up.

989
00:55:49,076 --> 00:55:50,619
She probably went to get her car.

990
00:55:52,287 --> 00:55:55,832
If we go now,
we can get there before her.

991
00:55:55,916 --> 00:55:58,085
Fucking Cha Yujin.
STYLE
::cue()

992
00:55:58,168 --> 00:56:01,630
[car engine revving]

993
00:56:01,713 --> 00:56:04,716
[lights buzzing]

994
00:56:16,603 --> 00:56:17,604
[car alarm beeps]

995
00:56:28,532 --> 00:56:29,908
[grunts]

996
00:56:29,991 --> 00:56:31,743
[car door opens]

997
00:56:31,827 --> 00:56:33,078
Huh?

998
00:56:33,161 --> 00:56:34,162
[car door closes]

999
00:56:35,539 --> 00:56:36,540
Cha Yujin?

1000
00:56:38,875 --> 00:56:39,876
Yes.

1001
00:56:41,169 --> 00:56:42,170
[chuckles]

1002
00:56:44,548 --> 00:56:46,133
Where's the casket?

1003
00:56:47,467 --> 00:56:48,468
Huh?

1004
00:56:51,138 --> 00:56:53,432
[Yujin] Uh, the casket?

1005
00:56:58,520 --> 00:56:59,521
[Yujin grunting]

1006
00:56:59,604 --> 00:57:02,607
[both struggling]

1007
00:57:02,691 --> 00:57:04,651
-[gasping]
- Fucking bitch.

1008
00:57:05,444 --> 00:57:07,529
I'm afraid I'm a little impatient.

1009
00:57:07,612 --> 00:57:09,406
So I don't have time to listen
to your excuses.

1010
00:57:09,489 --> 00:57:11,032
Sorry about that.

1011
00:57:11,116 --> 00:57:12,325
I'll ask one more time.

1012
00:57:12,409 --> 00:57:15,287
[Yujin gasping]

1013
00:57:15,370 --> 00:57:17,497
Where's the gold.

1014
00:57:17,581 --> 00:57:20,584
[Yujin gasping]

1015
00:57:20,667 --> 00:57:23,545
No! I-I didn't steal it!
I didn't-

1016
00:57:23,628 --> 00:57:25,464
-What I took-
-Really?

1017
00:57:25,547 --> 00:57:28,675
-[Hocheol grunting]
-[Yujin gasping]

1018
00:57:37,851 --> 00:57:38,852
[Kang] Take this call.

1019
00:57:45,025 --> 00:57:46,067
[grunts]

1020
00:57:49,446 --> 00:57:51,156
[exhales]
Hello?

1021
00:57:51,239 --> 00:57:53,492
[Yujin] Do-Dokyung.

1022
00:57:53,575 --> 00:57:56,912
[Yujin gasping]

1023
00:57:56,995 --> 00:57:58,163
Yujin.

1024
00:57:58,246 --> 00:57:59,623
Captain, right now...

1025
00:58:00,957 --> 00:58:03,543
...your girlfriend is about
to take her last breath.

1026
00:58:03,627 --> 00:58:06,338
Whether she lives or dies
all depends on you.

1027
00:58:06,421 --> 00:58:08,840
Where's the casket?

1028
00:58:08,924 --> 00:58:10,425
[Yujin gagging]

1029
00:58:10,509 --> 00:58:14,346
[Hocheol] Fuck. Better speak up.
She's about to die.

1030
00:58:16,139 --> 00:58:18,308
[Yujin screaming]

1031
00:58:20,268 --> 00:58:21,770
I don't know.

1032
00:58:21,853 --> 00:58:25,273
[Yujin] The mine! The mine! The mine!
It's in the mine. There's a mine.

1033
00:58:25,357 --> 00:58:26,817
[Hocheol] Which mine?

1034
00:58:26,900 --> 00:58:28,193
[Hocheol snarls]

1035
00:58:28,276 --> 00:58:29,569
[Yujin] Here.

1036
00:58:29,653 --> 00:58:31,571
[Yujin breathing erratically]

1037
00:58:31,655 --> 00:58:33,698
[coughs]
[Yujin] Here.

1038
00:58:33,782 --> 00:58:36,451
[breathing heavily]

1039
00:58:36,535 --> 00:58:40,664
[Yujin] Wh-When you-when you get
to the end of National Route 7,

1040
00:58:40,747 --> 00:58:43,917
inside the very end is drift number eight.

1041
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:45,293
That's where it is.

1042
00:58:46,837 --> 00:58:48,547
[Yujin] I'm sorry!

1043
00:58:48,630 --> 00:58:51,424
I'm sorry! I swear I didn't steal it!
Please let me live! No!

1044
00:58:51,508 --> 00:58:53,635
Stop, no! Please no!

1045
00:58:53,718 --> 00:58:57,389
[Yujin gasping]

1046
00:58:57,472 --> 00:58:58,974
[both struggling]

1047
00:58:59,057 --> 00:59:00,517
Yujin?

1048
00:59:00,600 --> 00:59:04,187
[Hocheol snarling]

1049
00:59:04,271 --> 00:59:06,731
[Yujin gagging]

1050
00:59:15,198 --> 00:59:18,201
[Hocheol breathing heavily]

1051
00:59:24,541 --> 00:59:25,625
[phone beeps]

1052
00:59:28,211 --> 00:59:29,212
Heeju.

1053
00:59:31,840 --> 00:59:33,508
[Dokyung] Heeju, it's me, Dokyung.

1054
00:59:33,592 --> 00:59:34,885
Park found out about the gold bars.

1055
00:59:34,968 --> 00:59:36,386
Move them fast.

1056
00:59:41,266 --> 00:59:42,267
[gold bars clink]
STYLE
::cue()

1057
00:59:58,033 --> 01:00:01,036
[grunting]

1058
01:00:02,871 --> 01:00:03,872
Shit.

1059
01:00:03,955 --> 01:00:06,958
[bars clinking]

1060
01:00:40,784 --> 01:00:43,787
[♪ dramatic music]

1061
01:00:50,919 --> 01:00:55,548
[Male Singer] ♪ Another day another hour ♪

1062
01:00:55,632 --> 01:00:59,928
♪ Free falling in my mind ♪

1063
01:01:00,011 --> 01:01:07,018
♪ I will find all of the reasons
for leaving ♪

1064
01:01:09,354 --> 01:01:14,442
♪ When everyone around me's changing ♪

1065
01:01:14,526 --> 01:01:18,905
♪ Everyone but me ♪

1066
01:01:18,989 --> 01:01:23,326
♪ All the things I thought I could be ♪

1067
01:01:24,411 --> 01:01:26,871
♪ Are out of reach ♪

1068
01:01:28,790 --> 01:01:33,378
♪ I leave it all behind ♪

1069
01:01:33,461 --> 01:01:37,424
♪ As you fall in line ♪

1070
01:01:37,507 --> 01:01:42,012
♪ I'm not expecting any light
at your door ♪

1071
01:01:42,095 --> 01:01:43,763
♪ There's nothing left ♪

1072
01:01:43,847 --> 01:01:50,103
♪ Just the pieces of everything
we could have been before ♪

1073
01:01:50,186 --> 01:01:54,399
♪ Evermore ♪

1074
01:01:54,482 --> 01:02:00,321
♪ I don't feel it like I used to ♪

1075
01:02:00,405 --> 01:02:02,657
♪ Anymore ♪

1076
01:02:15,295 --> 01:02:19,883
♪ You could find me in the dark ♪

1077
01:02:19,966 --> 01:02:24,179
♪ Still calling through the night ♪

1078
01:02:24,262 --> 01:02:29,142
♪ I leave behind all of the seasons ♪

1079
01:02:29,225 --> 01:02:31,895
I've dreamed of ♪

1080
01:02:34,272 --> 01:02:41,196
♪ But the water's rising over
everything I've known ♪

1081
01:02:41,279 --> 01:02:47,285
♪ Drifting out here all alone ♪

1082
01:02:48,912 --> 01:02:52,999
♪ On your own ♪

1083
